ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Just 3 to 4 days after the detection of new cases, the end of the South
Korean outbreak is too early to predict. The authorities have reportedly
taken rigorous steps to contain the disease in the pig farms. It would be
interesting to be informed about the steps taken by them to prevent virus
introduction into cattle holdings, which might occur by aerosols when pigs
-- efficient virus disseminators -- are involved. Is vaccination
practiced?! - Mod.AS].
